  Change: 6486b26553336c8575d1859ea8647a97292c3d6f
  Author: Doug Bell <madcityzen@gmail.com>
  Date : 2014-06-21 21:50:55 +0000

    cache page objects so we can modify them

    This is explicitly for spooky action at a distance to fix the
    following problem:

    * Blog app creates an index page and a feed page for that index *
    Site takes the index page and creates a new page with the same

    information but a new URL * Feed page no longer knows where the index
    page is

    Instead, the app gives us the same Page object whenever we ask, so we
    can modify it to make it our site index. 

  Change: faccb8d3737d5d8f0810a1460e48867bcd7b588d
  Author: Doug Bell <madcityzen@gmail.com>
  Date : 2014-06-21 20:46:30 +0000

    add feed pages

    Feed pages wrap a list page to provide another view of the page. This
    allows us to keep track of the list page's URL in case it changes, so
    that the feed page can link the user to the right location. 

  Change: aa809e76a30713da148d1de363781123a98d1241
